16:22.245 --> 16:24.247
[ Sniffles ]

16:28.291 --> 16:30.654
[ Both panting ]

16:32.455 --> 16:34.376
[ Dog tags clack ]

16:34.377 --> 16:37.419
I want to be buried with these.

16:37.420 --> 16:38.862
-That's a little morbid.

16:40.784 --> 16:42.385
-I want to be buried with them.

16:44.027 --> 16:48.390
When I go to heaven,
if that's where I'm going,

16:48.391 --> 16:50.112
I'm gonna hold them up to God,

16:50.113 --> 16:52.314
and I'm gonna ask
for an explanation.

16:52.315 --> 16:54.396
-He was old.

16:54.397 --> 16:56.599
- If I... If I did that...
If I blinded a dog

16:56.600 --> 16:59.041
and I shattered his hip
so he could barely move,

16:59.042 --> 17:01.283
so he could barely move
out of his own filth,

17:01.284 --> 17:03.285
that would make me
a psychopath, right?

17:03.286 --> 17:04.887
- Nora...
- No. It would, right?

17:04.887 --> 17:06.407
I mean, it... it would.

17:06.409 --> 17:08.851
God does that
over and over and over again,

17:08.852 --> 17:10.291
day in, day out,
every single day of the week

17:10.292 --> 17:11.534
and twice on Sunday.

17:11.535 --> 17:13.015
- You're a doctor,
for Christ's sake.

17:13.016 --> 17:15.858
You know how this works.

17:15.858 --> 17:17.299
-Yeah. That doesn't...

17:17.300 --> 17:19.622
That doesn't mean
I have to like it.

17:19.623 --> 17:22.263
- So, what? We're gonna
go through this all again?

17:22.265 --> 17:24.747
What's the point?
Why am I here?

17:24.748 --> 17:28.111
- I'm going to keep asking those
questions until I get answers.

17:29.593 --> 17:31.674
- Yeah, well,
good luck with that.

17:31.675 --> 17:34.356
- [ Scoffs ] You know what?
You're right.

17:34.357 --> 17:37.560
Fuck Him.
Fuck God.

17:37.561 --> 17:40.643
Fu... I don't want
to do this anymore.

17:40.644 --> 17:42.846
-What, this?

17:44.648 --> 17:45.888
-Yeah.

17:45.889 --> 17:47.449
-Why not?

17:47.450 --> 17:49.331
Because, uh... because
you don't want

17:49.332 --> 17:51.253
to have the same arguments
about theology

17:51.254 --> 17:54.177
that we had once a month
when we were married?

17:55.819 --> 17:57.580
-I don't...

17:57.581 --> 18:00.743
I guess I just don't.

18:00.744 --> 18:02.746
♫♫

18:05.589 --> 18:08.270
[ Dog barking in distance ]

18:08.271 --> 18:10.793
- You don't think
he has a drug problem, do you?

18:10.794 --> 18:13.597
- No.
I think it was a <i>girl</i> problem.

18:16.760 --> 18:19.161
This séance...

18:19.162 --> 18:20.643
We need to find another way.

18:20.644 --> 18:22.325
- No. This is the way.
Really.

18:24.167 --> 18:25.447
-$1.7 million.

18:25.448 --> 18:27.249
-Closer to 1.8.

18:27.250 --> 18:29.692
- Oh, God.
That is get-out-of-town money.

18:29.693 --> 18:33.096
New-life money,
an honest-to-God chance.

18:34.738 --> 18:36.018
We're putting our future

18:36.019 --> 18:38.100
in the hands
of some Vegas hustler.

18:38.101 --> 18:42.945
- No, the future is in <i>my</i> hands,
not <i>our</i> hands.

18:42.946 --> 18:46.669
Gina is a tool of the trade...
A deck of cards, a crystal ball.

18:46.670 --> 18:48.672
We will use her
to get what we want.

18:55.358 --> 18:58.842
- I just think she can
make things complicated.

19:03.607 --> 19:05.609
[ Light switch clicks ]

19:11.414 --> 19:13.416
[ Insects chirping ]

19:19.783 --> 19:23.186
[ Horn honking ]

19:37.480 --> 19:39.001
[ Honking stops ]

19:39.002 --> 19:41.364
[ Dogs barking in distance ]

19:44.848 --> 19:46.850
[ Horn honks ]

19:48.692 --> 19:50.092
-It's 3:00 in the morning.

19:50.093 --> 19:52.094
-What happened to my cat door?

19:52.095 --> 19:56.539
- I'll have the crew by
in the morning.

19:56.540 --> 19:59.181
And the next time you have
a problem, try calling.

19:59.182 --> 20:01.223
-People block me.

20:01.224 --> 20:02.825
-Can't imagine why.

20:02.826 --> 20:04.667
I'm not your errand boy.

20:04.668 --> 20:05.828
-Sure.

20:05.829 --> 20:07.710
-I'm gonna go back in,

20:07.711 --> 20:08.991
and I'm gonna go to sleep,

20:08.992 --> 20:10.513
and I will see you
in the morning.

20:10.514 --> 20:12.555
-I need Gold Bond cream.

20:12.556 --> 20:13.676
-What?

20:13.677 --> 20:15.277
-I need Gold Bond cream.

20:15.278 --> 20:16.879
-For the shop?

20:16.880 --> 20:19.201
- For my heels.
They crack.

20:19.202 --> 20:22.444
- Go to CVS.
It's open 24 hours.

20:22.445 --> 20:23.687
It's on Victory.

20:25.529 --> 20:29.572
[ Horn honks ]

20:29.573 --> 20:31.575
[ Dogs barking ]

20:34.057 --> 20:36.299
[ Horn honks ]

20:38.822 --> 20:41.384
[ Horn honks ]

20:42.626 --> 20:44.426
Fine.

20:44.427 --> 20:46.669
I'll bring the Gold Bond cream
first thing in the morning,

20:46.670 --> 20:48.431
and I'll have a crew there
for the cat door.

21:08.812 --> 21:10.933
-[ Chuckles nervously ]

21:10.934 --> 21:13.416
-Let us join together.

21:15.499 --> 21:16.899
-Gina will guide you.

21:16.900 --> 21:18.741
You're in good hands.

21:18.742 --> 21:20.864
-Okay.

21:28.191 --> 21:30.193
-[ Sighs ]

21:33.476 --> 21:37.479
- As we prepare
to summon the spirits,

21:37.480 --> 21:40.042
let us take a moment
to open our hearts

21:40.043 --> 21:43.165
and receive
the gift of connection.

21:43.166 --> 21:45.167
Sometimes,

21:45.168 --> 21:48.532
connection is the only gift
we have to offer.

21:51.454 --> 21:55.217
And connection is one
of the most powerful blessings

21:55.218 --> 21:57.339
the universe can give us.

21:57.340 --> 22:00.342
When two souls are joined,

22:00.343 --> 22:03.666
there is no power
on earth or in heaven

22:03.667 --> 22:05.669
that can keep them apart.

22:11.234 --> 22:14.517
The heart wants
what the heart wants.

22:14.518 --> 22:17.600
Please say the name of your boy.

22:17.601 --> 22:22.605
- I named him Miles.
Um, his family called him Dylan.

22:22.606 --> 22:27.129
- Then we will call him Miles
just as you did.

22:27.130 --> 22:30.452
We will ask
that he now cross the border,

22:30.453 --> 22:34.577
for we know
love is stronger than death.

22:34.578 --> 22:37.379
- Oh! Oh! Oh!
[ Children laugh in distance ]

22:37.380 --> 22:38.621
Oh.

22:38.622 --> 22:40.062
-Everybody all right?

22:40.063 --> 22:41.384
-Yeah.

22:47.150 --> 22:48.230
-Go! Go! Go!

22:48.231 --> 22:49.872
-Just a couple of kids playing.

22:49.873 --> 22:51.635
I am so sorry.

22:52.956 --> 22:56.839
-I think it's a sign.

22:56.840 --> 22:59.522
He's sending us a message.

22:59.523 --> 23:01.124
-Miles.

23:03.727 --> 23:05.689
He loved baseball.

23:08.091 --> 23:11.854
- Miles, you have made
your presence known.

23:11.855 --> 23:14.376
Tell us what you want.

23:14.377 --> 23:18.301
Let us into your life
as we want you in ours.

23:24.267 --> 23:26.949
Mm.

23:26.950 --> 23:29.391
Oh.

23:29.392 --> 23:32.395
He's saying
he wants to speak with us.

23:34.077 --> 23:35.839
- Is there anything
you want to say to him?

23:47.971 --> 23:55.971
-Miles, this is, uh... Mom.

23:56.019 --> 23:57.820
[ Chuckles ]

23:57.821 --> 24:00.062
Oh.

24:00.063 --> 24:05.067
I've been wanting
to say this to you...

24:05.068 --> 24:07.150
for a long time.

24:10.994 --> 24:12.555
[ Inhales deeply ]

24:12.556 --> 24:17.760
I love you.
I love you.

24:17.761 --> 24:19.843
♫♫

24:22.365 --> 24:24.928
[ Cries ]

24:33.456 --> 24:35.618
- There are other ways
of looking at it...

24:35.619 --> 24:37.860
Kids playing, coincidence.

24:37.861 --> 24:41.263
But, as I said before,
I have seen some things,

24:41.264 --> 24:43.305
and this was definitely
one of them.

24:43.306 --> 24:46.148
-A connection... I feel it.

24:46.149 --> 24:49.231
You have a son.
You know.

24:49.232 --> 24:54.356
I mean, it's a connection
you cannot describe,

24:54.357 --> 24:56.198
a bond that nothing can break.

24:56.199 --> 24:57.600
-Of course.

24:57.601 --> 25:00.082
- Yes.
You just know.

25:00.083 --> 25:02.284
[ Echoing ] I can't tell you
how grateful I am

25:02.285 --> 25:03.687
for all your love and support.

25:07.290 --> 25:09.211
[ Tea kettle whistling ]

25:09.212 --> 25:13.215
think I would ever
be able to connect with Miles.

25:13.216 --> 25:14.817
[ Whistling continues ]

25:14.818 --> 25:17.861
[ Man screams ]

25:21.865 --> 25:24.146
[ Man screams ]

25:24.147 --> 25:26.268
-Honey?

25:26.269 --> 25:28.190
[ Whistling stops ]

25:28.191 --> 25:29.832
-Are you okay?

25:29.833 --> 25:32.354
- [ Sighs ] Yeah, I'm fine.

25:32.355 --> 25:38.440
Uh, it's just been a very
overwhelming experience today.

25:38.441 --> 25:41.284
Would you excuse me
for one minute?

25:44.528 --> 25:45.888
[ Door closes ]
- Pretty sweet.

25:45.889 --> 25:48.410
The ball hit right on time.

25:48.411 --> 25:50.092
So, what's next?

25:50.093 --> 25:52.054
Charge her every time
she wants to talk to the kid?

25:52.055 --> 25:53.896
I mean, we could explain

25:53.897 --> 25:56.378
there's some kind of psychic
disturbance blocking him.

25:56.379 --> 25:58.340
She'd have to pay extra
to get rid of it.

25:58.341 --> 25:59.662
-We're done.

25:59.663 --> 26:02.424
- With Nadine?
We just got started.

26:02.425 --> 26:05.227
- Linda has itches
she needs to scratch.

26:05.228 --> 26:08.751
From time to time, she does.
I understand that.

26:08.752 --> 26:11.635
I'm sensing emotion here.

26:13.076 --> 26:14.678
Feelings.

26:16.399 --> 26:21.004
And that's not gonna work
for me, for my family.

26:24.087 --> 26:26.369
It's time for you to go.

26:28.051 --> 26:30.773
- Maybe she wants
to keep scratching.

26:30.774 --> 26:33.737
- We can go into the kitchen.
We can ask her.

26:36.259 --> 26:38.781
Don't bother saying goodbyes.

26:38.782 --> 26:41.024
I'll take care of that.

26:42.425 --> 26:45.748
- You focus on the simple,
I think.

26:45.749 --> 26:47.389
[ Door opens ]
So...

26:47.390 --> 26:48.671
[ Door closes ]

26:48.672 --> 26:49.992
I don't know.

26:49.993 --> 26:51.834
So I'll have to process it.

26:51.835 --> 26:53.836
- Nadine,
can I walk you to your car?

26:53.837 --> 26:56.319
- Oh, please.
Thank you.

26:58.241 --> 27:00.804
♫♫

27:10.373 --> 27:12.375
[ Horn honks ]

27:23.667 --> 27:25.467
- I sent my crew
for the cat door.

27:25.468 --> 27:28.230
They said they'd be there
at 11:00.

27:28.231 --> 27:31.754
-They're working now.

27:31.755 --> 27:33.475
-Well, then, what's the problem?

27:33.476 --> 27:36.478
- I came to re-up on candles,
but you know what?

27:36.479 --> 27:38.480
I don't care about candles
anymore.

27:38.481 --> 27:40.683
Who's she?

27:40.684 --> 27:43.285
-A client.

27:43.286 --> 27:45.127
- Fancy lady.
Fancy car.

27:45.128 --> 27:46.408
-We don't discriminate.

27:46.409 --> 27:47.810
-You tell Fonso?

27:47.811 --> 27:49.251
-That I have a rich client?

27:49.252 --> 27:50.894
I have a few of them.

27:53.176 --> 27:54.777
-You're working her long.

27:54.778 --> 27:57.219
- [ Scoffs ]
We're strictly short.

27:57.220 --> 27:58.501
-I don't think so.

27:58.502 --> 28:00.743
-Her husband's cheating on her.

28:00.744 --> 28:01.904
We're helping her with that.

28:01.905 --> 28:03.986
Anything deeper,
we hand to Fonso.

28:03.987 --> 28:04.987
That's the deal.

28:04.988 --> 28:06.789
-Well, I'll tell him, then.

28:06.790 --> 28:09.752
We'll let him decide whether
you're working long or short.

28:09.753 --> 28:11.754
- Come in the house.
You want to call him?

28:11.755 --> 28:15.158
- I got my cellphone.
We don't have to go anywhere.

28:22.766 --> 28:24.286
-What do you want?

28:24.287 --> 28:27.491
- Give me my piece
or I tell Fonso.

28:31.014 --> 28:33.216
[ Engine starts ]

28:35.098 --> 28:37.100
[ Engine squeals ]

28:39.583 --> 28:41.585
♫♫

28:43.306 --> 28:45.628
- He was in the shower.
I told him to get dressed.

28:45.629 --> 28:47.830
- So, we'll be waiting here
for another half hour.

28:47.831 --> 28:49.632
-[ Laughs ]

28:49.633 --> 28:52.716
Teenage standard time.
You could set your watch by it.

28:55.839 --> 28:57.920
Do you think she'll tell Fonso?

28:57.921 --> 28:59.962
-If we don't pay her.

28:59.963 --> 29:01.564
-If we do?

29:01.565 --> 29:03.806
- Nothing's stopping her
from coming back for more.

29:03.807 --> 29:07.009
She'll hold it over us forever.

29:07.010 --> 29:08.851
-Options?

29:08.852 --> 29:12.174
-One, we cut her in.

29:12.175 --> 29:13.415
-No fucking way.

29:13.416 --> 29:16.979
- Okay.
We get ahead of the story.

29:16.980 --> 29:19.141
We tell Fonso
we were playing Nadine short,

29:19.142 --> 29:20.823
but we found something.

29:20.824 --> 29:23.025
- Give her up?
- You asked for options.

29:23.026 --> 29:26.789
- Fucking can't believe
this shit.

29:26.790 --> 29:29.231
You fucking...
You saw Nadine in there.

29:29.232 --> 29:30.272
She's this close.

29:30.273 --> 29:31.874
-I said it was an option.

29:31.875 --> 29:34.316
I didn't say
it's what I wanted to do.

29:34.317 --> 29:35.878
-[ Sighs ]

29:35.879 --> 29:37.800
- There was a different vibe
in the room today.

29:37.801 --> 29:41.443
- Yeah, of course.
We're going for the big game.

29:41.444 --> 29:45.649
- No.
It was something different.

29:55.979 --> 29:58.261
-What did you say to her?

30:00.383 --> 30:03.507
-I told her to leave.

30:06.429 --> 30:09.031
- You're the one
that brought her back in.

30:09.032 --> 30:10.713
- Yeah,
I don't think now's the time

30:10.714 --> 30:14.036
to be pointing a finger at me.

30:14.037 --> 30:16.039
♫♫

30:20.123 --> 30:22.245
There was something different
this time.

30:25.328 --> 30:30.093
Like... you crossed a line.

30:35.058 --> 30:36.900
-It's over.

30:40.704 --> 30:43.465
- We never make each other
the mark.

30:43.466 --> 30:45.668
That was our deal.

30:45.669 --> 30:49.192
The only people we're honest
with are each other.

30:51.995 --> 30:54.557
Nadine's money... like you said,

30:54.558 --> 30:58.601
we get a total reboot,
no more Roma, no more parlors.

30:58.602 --> 31:01.844
But there can't be distractions!

31:01.845 --> 31:03.886
No secrets!

31:03.887 --> 31:05.689
-I know.

31:08.652 --> 31:10.654
[ Sighs ]

31:16.259 --> 31:18.542
So, Fabiana?

31:21.985 --> 31:24.627
- Yeah.
I'll talk to Eduardo.

31:24.628 --> 31:27.229
- I guess you were right about
having a gangster on our side.

31:27.230 --> 31:29.232
[ Door opens, closes ]

31:33.316 --> 31:34.797
[ Car door closes ]

31:34.798 --> 31:36.799
- "Sorry to keep you waiting,
parents."

31:36.800 --> 31:38.602
-What?

31:40.283 --> 31:41.764
[ Engine starts ]

31:41.765 --> 31:43.767
♫♫

31:50.413 --> 31:52.815
- ♫ <i>Well I came at you</i>
<i>a young boy, girl</i> ♫

31:52.816 --> 31:56.979
- The key is to marinate.
My secret's Sunny D.

31:56.980 --> 31:59.301
That shit
gets right into the meat.

31:59.302 --> 32:03.225
Leave it for 24 hours... bang.
Flavor explosion.

32:03.226 --> 32:05.347
The rest is just keeping
the flame off the meat

32:05.348 --> 32:06.749
so it doesn't char.

32:06.750 --> 32:09.552
It's not rocket science.
The cave men did it.

32:09.553 --> 32:11.794
- Read my palm.
Right now.

32:11.795 --> 32:13.355
-She's trying to relax, man.

32:13.356 --> 32:15.237
- No, no.
I'll do it.

32:15.238 --> 32:17.520
-How's your plan going?

32:17.521 --> 32:19.802
-Plan?

32:19.803 --> 32:22.284
- "Top of the food chain."
Isn't that what you said?

32:22.285 --> 32:25.528
-I got some irons in the fire.

32:25.529 --> 32:27.329
[ Music continues over stereo ]

32:27.330 --> 32:29.012
- I never thought
I'd get to see that.

32:34.698 --> 32:37.419
You need me to fan
the flames of that fire,

32:37.420 --> 32:38.942
you just let me know.

32:41.104 --> 32:43.345
-It's so clear.

32:43.346 --> 32:44.627
-What?

32:44.628 --> 32:46.509
-You're single.

32:46.510 --> 32:48.831
- How can you tell?
My love line?

32:48.832 --> 32:52.234
- No, it's the calluses,
the blisters.

32:52.235 --> 32:53.996
You jack off way too much.

32:53.997 --> 32:55.719
[ Laughter ]

32:57.200 --> 33:00.243
- You're good.
Pretty fucking good.

33:01.725 --> 33:04.887
- For what it's worth,
I'd give my left nut

33:04.888 --> 33:08.090
if I never have to fry
another guy in oil.

33:08.091 --> 33:09.411
See those guys?

33:09.412 --> 33:11.014
I mean,
those are my oldest friends.

33:12.856 --> 33:15.818
They'd buy tickets
to watch that happen.

33:15.819 --> 33:19.181
Again, like in your business,
it takes all kinds.

33:19.182 --> 33:20.623
Now, I'm gonna tell you this

33:20.624 --> 33:24.026
'cause obviously
we have a rapport and all.

33:24.027 --> 33:25.789
I've got a dream.

33:27.791 --> 33:29.512
I'm a notary.

33:29.513 --> 33:31.914
I got my license
three weeks ago.

33:31.915 --> 33:34.036
- That's great.
- I'm going into real estate,

33:34.037 --> 33:35.518
and I'm gonna do it all
myself...

33:35.519 --> 33:38.360
The paperwork and everything.

33:38.361 --> 33:39.922
Listen...
Like in all businesses,

33:39.923 --> 33:41.604
I'm gonna eliminate
the middle man.

33:41.605 --> 33:43.806
Do you want in?

33:43.807 --> 33:47.369
Once I'm up and running,
I will hook you up.

33:47.370 --> 33:49.411
It's gonna be completely
above board.

33:49.412 --> 33:53.375
Legit, honest,
it's a sweet deal.

33:53.376 --> 33:56.699
[ Echoing ] I mean,
we all want to get out, man.

33:56.700 --> 33:58.741
I mean, maybe not my partners.

33:58.742 --> 34:01.183
They want to make their money
working the streets.

34:01.184 --> 34:04.426
[ Slow-mo ] They're not
embracing the vision.

34:04.427 --> 34:08.150
[ Fire crackling,
man screaming ]

34:22.525 --> 34:24.887
- Hey!
What the...

34:24.888 --> 34:27.409
What's wrong with you?

34:27.409 --> 34:30.092
Come on.

34:30.092 --> 34:32.775
[ Music continues over stereo ]

34:32.775 --> 34:35.899
[ Crowd murmuring ]

34:39.902 --> 34:42.545
- [ Normal voice ]
My man, you're the one.

34:42.545 --> 34:44.947
You're the one who knows.

34:44.947 --> 34:47.268
You're the one with the power.

34:47.270 --> 34:48.831
Come on.

34:48.831 --> 34:50.272
I'm gonna get you
a drink of the good shit.

34:50.273 --> 34:53.114
I want you to tell me
what you saw.

34:53.116 --> 34:56.318
[ Indistinct chatter ]

34:56.319 --> 34:58.321
[ Laughter ]

35:02.085 --> 35:03.405
- Oh, great.
Thanks.

35:03.406 --> 35:05.768
[ Latin music playing
over stereo ]

35:05.769 --> 35:08.410
- Is this a vision
I should know about?

35:08.411 --> 35:09.852
-I don't know what it was.

35:09.853 --> 35:12.174
I don't even know
if it was a vision.

